          <h5 class="bold" style="padding-top: 10px;">How do I use the Classroom Mapping Tool?
          </h5>
          <!--<h6 class="bold text-secondary">09/20/2019</h6>-->
          <p class="text-secondary">
            The Classroom Mapping Tool can be used in several ways. It was created to allow teachers a visual way of sharing student feeling feedback to different parts of the classroom. The tool can be used for teachers to collect the data independently after a class period or length of time where students are independently and throughout the class giving feedback or it can be used during class and filled out together to start the conversation of feelings in different parts of the classroom. The second approach can be seen on the Homepage collection of student maps.
          </p>

        </div>
