          <h5 class="bold" style="padding-top: 10px;">How do I gather data and know what areas of the classroom are Green Spaces and Pink Spaces?
          </h5>
          <!--<h6 class="bold text-secondary">09/20/2019</h6>-->
          <p class="text-secondary">
            Our first recommended approach is for teachers can either give students pink and green post-itâ€™s and co-define what each color means with their students. Our second recommended approach is to have students fill out the Classroom Mapping Tool as partners or groups. Our third recommended approach is to collect data from the post-it notes after the activity and label each pile, counting how many of each color came from each area of the room, then use the numbers to label using the directions on the Classroom Mapping Tool. 
          </p>

